.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20looking%20for%20a%20job%20in%20October.%20I%20applied%20for%20a%20bunch%20of%20jobs.%20I%20heard%20back%20from%20four%20of%20them.%20I%20added%20it%20up%20the%20other%20day%3A%20I%20have%20now%20been%20on%2017%20interviews%20across%20four%20jobs.%20And%20I%20actually%20did%20just%20get%20an%20offer%20from%20one%20though%20I%20don't%20think%20I'm%20going%20to%20take%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20others%2C%20it's%20fine%20if%20I%20don't%20get%20an%20offer%2C%20but%20at%20least%20just%20reject%20me%20already.%20But%20it%20seems%20like%20rather%20than%20rejecting%20me%2C%20they%20just%20seem%20to%20keep%20going%20%E2%80%94%20adding%20on%20another%20stage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20one%20job%2C%20which%20is%20like%20a%20hybrid%20role%2C%20I%20had%20two%20phone%20interviews%20and%20then%20they%20asked%20me%20to%20come%20in%2C%20which%20is%20fine.%20But%20they%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BCan%20you%20come%20in%20next%20week%20on%20this%20day%2C%20at%20this%20time%3F%20It's%20the%20only%20time%20slot%20we%20have%20available.%26quot%3B%20I%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BAlright.%20Fine%2C%20we'll%20just%20make%20it%20work.%26quot%3B%20They%20said%20in%20December%20they%20really%20wanted%20to%20wrap%20this%20up%20before%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year.%20So%20I%20go%20and%20interview%20in%20person%20with%20four%20people.%20And%20then%20here%20we%20are%20almost%20a%20month%20later%2C%20in%20January%2C%20and%20I%20have%20heard%20nothing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20the%20other%20two%20jobs%20are%20the%20two%20that%20have%20been%20insane.%20Unfortunately%2C%20I've%20interviewed%20for%20so%20many%20jobs%20over%20the%20past%20two%20or%20three%20years%20because%20when%20I%20was%20at%20one%20employer%2C%20I%20was%20really%20unhappy%20and%20was%20trying%20to%20leave.%20I%20got%20tons%20of%20interviews%20and%2C%20made%20it%20to%20final%20rounds%2C%20but%20just%20never%20could%20stick%20the%20landing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20I%20took%20a%20job%20at%20a%20startup.%20The%20startup%20five%20months%20later%20shut%20down%20and%20I%20got%20laid%20off.%20So%20then%20I%20had%20to%20do%20a%20new%20round%20of%20applying%20and%20interviewing.%20Then%20I%20took%20my%20most%20recent%20job%2C%20which%20was%20a%20terrible%20fit%20and%20I%20was%20very%20unhappy.%20So%20within%20three%20months%20of%20starting%20that%20job%2C%20I%20started%20applying%20and%20interviewing%20for%20more%20jobs.%20I%20feel%20like%20I've%20just%20been%20in%20a%20nonstop%20job%20interview%20cycle%20for%20two%20years%20now.%20It's%20all%20so%20insane.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHaving%20so%20many%20interviews%20makes%20me%20question%20the%20hiring%20process%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20even%20have%20to%20prepare%20really%20anymore%20because%20I've%20done%20it%20so%20many%20times.%20Particularly%20in%20this%20round%2C%20nobody's%20asked%20me%20a%20question%20that%20I%20haven't%20already%20been%20asked.%20So%20I%20have%20all%20the%20examples%20ready.%20It's%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20tell%20me%20about%20a%20time%20when%20blah%20blah%20blah.%26quot%3B%20It's%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20yeah%2C%20I%20know%20what%20to%20say%20for%20that%20one.%26quot%3B%20I've%20got%20all%20the%20like%20scenarios%20worked%20out.%20So%20I%20guess%20in%20that%20sense%2C%20it%20is%20a%20little%20bit%20easier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20thinking%20about%20this%20the%20other%20day%3A%20Is%20this%20really%20the%20best%20way%20to%20determine%20whether%20you're%20a%20good%20fit%20for%20a%20job%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0having%20a%20couple%20of%2030-minute%20conversations%3F%20I%20mean%20I%20don't%20know%20what%20the%20alternative%20is.%20My%20last%20job%20was%20such%20a%20bad%20fit.%20It%20was%20like%2C%20is%20there%20anything%20I%20should%20have%20seen%3F%20I%20don't%20think%20so.%20It's%20not%20like%20companies%20are%20going%20to%20tell%20you%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%20yeah%2C%20we%20make%20you%20work%20long%20hours%20and%20we're%20not%20going%20to%20train%20you.%20We're%20not%20going%20to%20give%20you%20any%20support.%26quot%3B%20It's%20not%20like%20anybody's%20ever%20going%20to%20be%20honest%20about%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20always%20have%20to%20be%20on%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20there's%20this%20other%20job.%20I%20had%20the%20first%20screen%20with%20HR.%20I%20had%20an%20initial%20conversation%20with%20the%20hiring%20manager.%20He%20was%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20I'd%20love%20to%20continue%20this%20conversation.%26quot%3B%20So%20I%20had%20another%20conversation%20with%20him%20in%20which%20I%20was%20a%20little%20more%20prepared%20and%20studied%20up%20on%20their%20product%20and%20their%20company%20and%20had%20a%20little%20more%20sort%20of%20a%20targeted%20conversation%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20he%20had%20me%20talk%20to%20two%20people%20at%20the%20company%20who%20were%20supposed%20to%20be%20more%20sort%20of%20culture%20fit%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0more%20casual%20conversations.%20I%20feel%20like%20they%20say%20that.%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20yeah%2C%20it's%20just%20a%20casual%20conversation%20for%20you%20to%20ask%20questions.%26quot%3B%20But%20it's%20not%20like%20you%20can%20ever%20be%20casual%20when%20you're%20trying%20to%20get%20a%20job.%20You're%20always%20performing.%20And%20you%20always%20have%20to%20be%20on%20because%20they're%20evaluating%20you.%20And%20yeah%2C%20sure%2C%20you're%20evaluating%20them.%20But%20the%20stakes%20are%20not%20even.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20I%20had%20two%20of%20those%20interviews.%20I%20was%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BOK%2C%20cool.%20Probably%20we're%20done.%26quot%3B%20And%20then%20the%20following%20week%2C%20it%20was%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20I%20want%20you%20to%20talk%20to%20two%20more%20people.%26quot%3B%20Initially%2C%20that%20job%20was%20my%20top%20choice%20of%20the%20four.%20But%20for%20some%20reason%2C%20when%20that%20happened%2C%20it%20really%20just%20left%20a%20sour%20taste%20in%20my%20mouth.%20It%20really%20turned%20me%20off%20because%20I%20just%20feel%20like%20you're%20wasting%20my%20time.%20How%20much%20more%20do%20you%20need%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20get%20it%2C%20particularly%20at%20a%20small%20company.%20It's%20a%20startup.%20Every%20hire%20carries%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20weight%20versus%20if%20you're%20just%20another%20employee%20at%20IBM%20or%20Google%20or%20whatever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20it%20just%20feels%20like%20it's%20a%20waste%20of%20everyone's%20time.%20Since%20I've%20been%20interviewing%20for%20two%20years%2C%20there%20was%20one%20where%20they%20had%20me%20do%20an%20initial%20HR%20screening.%20Then%20I%20had%20a%20conversation%20with%20the%20hiring%20manager%20and%20they%20made%20me%20do%20five%20interviews%20of%2045%20minutes%20each.%20They%20were%20spaced%20out%20over%20a%20week%20or%20two.%20And%20then%20I%20just%20never%20even%20heard%20back%20from%20them.%20It%20was%20unbelievable%20because%20it%20was%20such%20a%20waste%20of%20my%20time%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0but%20also%20such%20a%20waste%20of%20their%20employees'%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20going%20through%20this%20again%20now.%20I%20had%20to%20do%20three%20panel%20interviews%20of%2045%20minutes%20each%2C%20which%20seems%20to%20be%20more%20of%20a%20thing%20at%20bigger%20companies.%20I'm%20always%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20if%20I'm%20doing%20these%2045-minute%20panels%2C%20that's%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20to%20invest.%26quot%3B%20Having%20your%20employees%20spend%20an%20hour%20each%20talking%20to%20somebody%2C%20I've%20got%20to%20be%20a%20finalist%2C%20right%3F%20But%20I%20don't%20know.%20Surely%20they're%20not%20putting%2010%20people%20through%20these%20hourslong%20processes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20did%20those%20two%20conversations%20for%20that%20startup%2C%20which%20ended%20up%20being%20like%20the%20sixth%20or%20seventh%20interviews%2C%20and%20then%20I%20was%20just%20sort%20of%20like%2C%20whatever.%20I%20have%20yet%20to%20hear%20anything%20back%20from%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20one%20I'm%20interviewing%20for%20now%2C%20I%20had%20a%20conversation%20with%20a%20recruiter%20in%20November.%20I%20didn't%20hear%20anything.%20I%20thought%20I%20didn't%20pass%20the%20screening.%20Finally%2C%20I%20heard%20from%20them%20after%20Christmas.%20Then%20I%20had%20the%20hiring%20manager%20call.%20That%20was%2045%20minutes%20and%20then%20I've%20had%20these%20three%2045-minute%20conversations%20and%20then%20there's%20one%20more%20beyond%20this.%20I'm%20just%20so%20exhausted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey're%20wasting%20my%20time%2C%20but%20they%20obviously%20don't%20care%20about%20my%20time%20because%20I'm%20nothing%20to%20them%20but%20a%20candidate.%20And%20they%20just%20have%20candidates%20lined%20out%20the%20door%2C%20particularly%20right%20now%2C%20where%20so%20many%20people%20are%20out%20of%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt's%20a%20total%20crapshoot%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20think%20having%20been%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20things%2C%20where%20I%20hired%20someone%2C%20I%20had%20just%20three%20rounds.%20And%20the%20person%20I%20ended%20up%20hiring%20was%20horrible.%20But%20she%20was%20great%20in%20the%20interviews.%20So%20it's%20also%20one%20of%20those%20things%20where%20I%20just%20feel%20like%2C%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20we're%20spending%20all%20this%20time%20doing%20all%20these%20interviews.%20Ultimately%2C%20it's%20a%20total%20crapshoot%20of%20whether%20that%20person%20actually%20does%20what%20they%20say%20they%20do%2C%20or%20whether%20they're%20just%20good%20at%20interviewing.%20Or%2C%20like%20in%20my%20case%2C%20where%20maybe%20they%20made%20the%20job%20sound%20really%20great.%20But%20then%20you%20take%20it%20and%20it%20turns%20out%20to%20be%20something%20totally%20different.%20All%20of%20this%20interviewing%20and%20all%20this%20time%20that%20we're%20spending%2C%20we%20might%20as%20well%20just%20be%20rolling%20the%20dice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%2C%20understandably%2C%20have%20wanted%20to%20spread%20the%20decision%20beyond%20just%20the%20hiring%20manager.%20It's%20also%20the%20people%20who%20are%20going%20to%20work%20with%20this%20person%20and%