980%2C000%20In%20Bank%20To%20Aus%20Open%20Show%20-%20Nagal's%20Current%20Prize%20Money%20Is...%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIndia's%20top-ranked%20singles%20tennis%20player%20Sumit%20Nagal%20stunned%20World%20Number%2027%20Alexander%20Bublik%20of%20Kazakstan%20to%20move%20to%20the%20second%20round%20of%20the%20Australian%20Open%202024%20on%20Tuesday.%20It%20was%20a%20sensational%20victory%20for%20Nagal%20as%20he%20won%C2%A06-4%2C%206-2%2C%207-6%20(7%2F5)%20in%20a%20match%20that%20lasted%20two%20hours%20and%2038%20minutes.%20This%20was%20the%20first%20time%20since%201989%20that%20an%20Indian%20tennis%20player%20beat%20a%20seeded%20opponent%20in%20a%20Grand%20Slam.%20The%20last%20instance%20was%20back%20in%201989%20when%C2%A0Ramesh%20Krishnan%20defeated%20Mats%20Wilander%2C%20the%20then%20world%20number%20one%20and%20defending%20champion%20at%20the%20Australian%20Open.%20This%20victory%20was%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20achievements%20in%20Nagal's%20career%20and%20a%20significant%20step%20forward%20for%20a%20tennis%20player%20who%20was%20in%20the%20headlines%20for%20his%20struggles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20Nagal%20shared%20his%20financial%20struggles%20and%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20PTI%2C%20that%20his%20annual%20budget%20to%20survive%20on%20the%20ATP%20Tour%20was%20around%20Rs%201%20crore%20and%20he%20had%20just%C2%A0around%20Rs%2080%2C000%20in%20his%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I%20look%20at%20my%20bank%20balance%2C%20I%20have%20what%20I%20had%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20year.%20It%20is%20900%20euros%20(approx%20Rs%2080%2C000).%20I%20did%20get%20a%20bit%20of%20help.%20Mr%20Prashant%20Sutar%20is%20helping%20me%20with%20MAHA%20Tennis%20Foundation%20and%20I%20also%20get%20monthly%20(salary)%20from%20IOCL%20but%20I%20don't%20have%20any%20big%20sponsor%2C%26quot%3B%20Nagal%20told%20PTI%20in%20an%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20interview%2C%20he%20received%20help%20from%C2%A0leading%20beverage%20company%20PepsiCo%20India%20and%20the%20Delhi%20Lawn%20Tennis%20Association%20(DLTA).%20The%20financial%20help%20was%20crucial%20for%20the%20tennis%20player%20and%20his%20journey%20in%20the%20Australian%20Open%20till%20now%20has%20been%20a%20perfect%20culmination%20of%20his%20journey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20not%20getting%20a%20wildcard%20entry%20to%20the%20Australian%20Open%2C%20Nagal%20took%20part%20in%20the%20qualification%20matches%20and%20with%20three%20wins%20on%20the%20trot%2C%20he%20booked%20his%20berth%20and%20also%20ended%20up%20earning%20around%20AUD%20120%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20win%20against%20Bublik%20earned%20Nagal%20another%20AUD%20180%2C000%20(Rs%2098%20lakh%20approximately)%20and%20with%20the%20victory%2C%20this%20became%20the%20first%20time%20that%20he%20reached%20the%C2%A0second%20round%20of%20the%20Australian%20Open.%C2%A0The%20world%20number%20137%20Indian%20will%20be%20playing%20in%20the%20second%20round%20of%20a%20Grand%20Slam%20for%20the%20second%20time%20in%20his%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENagal%20will%20now%20face%C2%A0wildcard%20Juncheng%20Shang%20of%20China%20in%20the%20second%20round%20where%20a%20win%20will%20create%20history%20for%20the%20tennis%20player%20and%20will%20also%20earn%20him%20somewhere%20around%20AUD%C2%A0255%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(With%20PTI%20inputs)%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705401660000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2Fv2gnnkuo_dd_625x300_16_January_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Faustralian-open-2024%2Fonly-80-000-in-bank-to-australian-open-2024-show-sumit-nagals-current-prize-money-is-4873221%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sumit%20Nagal%20stunned%20World%20Number%2027%20Alexander%20Bublik%20of%20Kazakstan%20to%20move%20to%20the%20second%20round%20of%20Australian%20Open%202024.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bilkis%20Bano's%20Long%20Struggle%20for%20Justice%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F17184203%2FBILKIS-BANO-.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiacable.com%2Fp%2Ftop-indian-army-generals-video-gets%3Futm_source%3Dpost-email-title%26publication_id%3D105593%26post_id%3D140697721%26utm_campaign%3Demail-post-title%26isFreemail%3Dtrue%26r%3D393wy%26utm_medium%3Demail%5C%22%3Ewas%20first%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20The%20India%20Cable%C2%A0%E2%80%93%20a%20premium%20newsletter%20from%20The%20Wire%20%26amp%3B%20Galileo%20Ideas%20%E2%80%93%20and%20has%20been%20republished%20here.%20To%20subscribe%20to%20The%20India%20Cable%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3Eclick%20here%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20quashing%20the%20Gujarat%20government%E2%80%99s%20grossly%20unjust%20order%20to%20release%20the%2011%20men%20sentenced%20to%20life%20imprisonment%20for%20gangrape%20and%20multiple%20murders%20in%20the%20Bilkis%20Bano%20case%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20noted%20that%20the%20release%20of%20the%20perpetrators%20marked%20a%20%E2%80%9Cusurpation%20of%20jurisdiction%20and%20an%20instance%20of%20abuse%20of%20discretion%E2%80%9D.%20The%20judgment%20of%20Justice%20Nagarathna%20and%20Justice%20Ujjal%20Bhuyan%20overruled%20the%20May%202022%20decision%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20which%20had%20said%20Gujarat%20was%20the%20appropriate%20government%20to%20decide%20the%20remission%20plea%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%201992%20remission%20and%20premature%20release%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBilkis%20Bano%20was%20a%20victim%20of%20egregious%20sexual%20violence%20but%20the%20case%20is%20not%20only%20about%20that%2C%20it%20is%20also%20about%20communal%20violence%20and%20state%20impunity.%20In%202002%2C%20communal%20violence%20became%20a%20strategic%20instrument%20of%20polarisation%20and%20mobilisation%20in%20Gujarat.%20This%20strategy%20adopted%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20violence%20changed%20the%20political%20landscape%20of%20the%20country.%20It%20also%20illustrates%20how%20legal%20provisions%20and%20laws%20can%20be%20subverted.%20After%20a%20prolonged%20legal%20battle%2C%20the%2011%20accused%20were%20sentenced%20to%20life%20imprisonment%20in%202008.%20But%20the%20case%20had%20to%20be%20shifted%20out%20of%20Gujarat%20to%20Maharashtra%20since%20Bilkis%20had%20received%20death%20threats%20and%20there%20were%20apprehensions%20that%20the%20victim%20would%20not%20receive%20a%20fair%20trial%20or%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20fears%20were%20borne%20out%20by%20the%20premature%20release%20of%20convicts%20on%20August%2015%2C%202022%2C%20by%20the%20Bhartiya%20Janata%20Party%20government%20which%20was%20in%20power%20during%20the%202002%20communal%20riots.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20noted%20that%20the%20state%20of%20Gujarat%20had%20%E2%80%9Cacted%20in%20complicity%20with%20the%20convicts%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20%E2%80%9Cit%20was%20this%20very%20apprehension%20which%20led%20this%20Court%20to%20transfer%20the%20trial%20out%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%9D%20to%20Maharashtra.%20In%20effect%2C%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20did%20not%20have%20any%20jurisdiction%20to%20decide%20on%20granting%20remission%20to%20convicts%20sentenced%20in%20Maharashtra.%20While%20pronouncing%20the%20verdict%2C%20the%20apex%20court%20stated%20that%20the%20government%20to%20decide%20on%20the%20remission%20is%20the%20state%20within%20whose%20jurisdiction%20the%20accused%20were%20sentenced%2C%20and%20not%20the%20state%20within%20whose%20territory%20the%20offence%20was%20committed.%20In%20view%20of%20this%20policy%2C%20the%20state%20government%20was%20guilty%20of%20usurpation%20of%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20grounds%20on%20which%20the%20remission%20was%20granted%20were%20manifestly%20political%20%E2%80%93%20the%20remission%20order%20was%20given%20in%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20the%20campaign%20for%20state%20assembly%20elections%20in%20Gujarat%20in%202022.%20Significantly%2C%20the%20highest%20courts%E2%80%99s%20verdict%20was%20an%20indictment%20of%20the%20Union%20government%20too%2C%20as%20the%20remission%20order%20was%20counter-signed%20by%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs.%20Sending%20the%20convicted%20men%20back%20to%20jail%20in%20these%20circumstances%20marks%20a%20pivotal%20moment%20for%20the%20pursuit%20of%20justice%20in%20the%20current%20political%20landscape.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fin-her-own-words-what-bilkis-bano-went-through-in-2002%5C%22%3EIn%20Her%20Own%20Words%3A%20What%20Bilkis%20Bano%20Went%20Through%20in%202002%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20one%20from%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20and%20none%20of%20those%20who%20matter%20in%20the%20state%20have%20said%20anything%20yet%20on%20the%20verdict.%20No%20ruling%20party%20leader%20has%20commented%20on%20the%20ruling%2C%20let%20alone%20welcoming%20it.%20The%20verdict%20got%20almost%20no%20mention%20in%20most%20of%20the%20television%20news%20channels%20and%20found%20no%20mention%20even%20in%20the%20national%20dailies%20beyond%20the%20first%20day%20of%20reporting.%20The%20media%20and%20middle%20classes%20have%20been%20largely%20silent%20on%20the%20unlawful%20remission%20and%20its%20reversal%2C%20even%20as%20they%20outrage%20over%20other%20cases%20of%20sexual%20violence%20and%20crimes%20against%20women.%20This%20calculated%20silence%20is%20part%20of%20the%20effort%20to%20erase%20the%20horrific%20violence%20and%20the%20unprecedented%20scale%20of%20gendered%20violence%20from%20public%20memory.%20For%20this%20reason%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20remember%20the%20Bilkis%20case%20as%20it%20reminds%20the%20country%20of%20a%20dark%20chapter%20in%20our%20history.%20Remembering%20it%20is%20crucial%20to%20prevent%20it%20from%20recurring.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20many%20attempts%20to%20silence%20her%2C%20Bilkis%20Bano%20persisted%20and%20emerged%20as%20a%20symbol%20of%20resistance.%20It%20was%20due%20to%20her%20perseverance%20and%20resistance%20that%20justice%20was%20delivered.%20But%20equally%2C%20we%20must%20also%20recognise%20the%20work%20and%20commitment%20of%20fearless%20lawyers%20and%20women%E2%80%99s%20rights%20activists%20who%20stood%20by%20her%20over%20the%20years.%20Feminist%20solidarities%20came%20to%20the%20forefront%20in%20all%20forms%20in%20these%20years%20%E2%80%93%20legal%20petitions%2C%20street%20protests%2C%20vigils%20and%20signature%20campaigns.%20These%20solidarities%20were%20particularly%20evident%20after%20the%20remission.%20Multiple%20pleas%20were%20filed%20by%20social%20activists%20against%20the%20remission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F10080129%2FUntitled-design-11.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F10080129%2FUntitled-design-11.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F10080129%2FUntitled-design-11-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F10080129%2FUntitled-design-11-1024x576.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-692216%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMahua%20Moitra%2C%20Revati%20Laul%2C%20Shobha%20Gupta%2C%20Bilkis%20Bano%2C%20Meeran%20Chadha%20Borwankar%2C%20Subhashini%20Ali%20and%20Roop%20Rekha%20Verma.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20notable%20was%20the%20work%20done%20by%20Bilkis%20Bano%E2%80%99s%20lawyer%20Shobha%20Gupta%2C%20who%20has%20backed%20her%20unwaveringly%20for%2020%20years.%20TMC%20member%20of%20parliament%20Mahua%20Moitra%20filed%20a%20petition.%20Another%20PIL%20was%20filed%20by%20Subhashini%20Ali%2C%20ex-MP%20and%20a%20member%20of%20the%20CPI(M)%2C%20journalist%20and%20author%20Revati%20Laul%2C%20and%20Professor%20Roop%20Rekha%20Verma%20of%20Lucknow%20University%2C%20challenging%20the%20Gujarat%20government%E2%80%99s%20remission%20and%20release%20order.%20Subsequently%2C%20another%20petition%20was%20filed%20by%20former%20IPS%20officer%20Meeran%20Chadha%20Borwankar%20in%20September%202022.%20The%20National%20Federation%20of%20Indian%20Women%20(NFIW)%20also%20filed%20a%20PIL%20challenging%20the%20release%20of%20the%20convicts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBilkis%20Bano%20has%20acknowledged%20the%20importance%20of%20feminist%20solidarities%20in%20her%20struggle%20for%20justice.%20She%20thanked%20the%20apex%20court%20for%20providing%20justice%20to%20her%20and%20her%20children%2C%20but%20she%20also%20thanked%20all%20the%20women%20for%20%E2%80%9Cthis%20vindication%20and%20hope%20in%20the%20promise%20of%20equal%20justice%20for%20all.%E2%80%9D%20It%20is%20a%20victory%20for%20not%20just%20this%20brave%20survivor%20of%20communal%20and%20sexual%20violence%20and%20warrior%20for%20justice%2C%20but%20also%20for%20everyone%20who%20fought%20for%20her%20and%20for%20justice%20to%20prevail.%20What%20emerges%20from%20this%20historic%20verdict%20is%20that%20the%20rule%20of%20law%2C%20above%20all%2C%20equality%20before%20law%20is%20for%20all%2C%20and%20is%20worth%20fighting%20for.%20This%20is%20a%20historic%20verdict%20because%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20very%20rarely%20declares%20its%20own%20judgment%20%E2%80%9Cnull%20and%20void%E2%80%9D%2C%20noted%20Indira%20Jaising%2C%20lawyer%20for%20Moitra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20the%20verdict%20%E2%80%9Cis%20a%20milestone%20on%20the%20journey%20of%20justice%E2%80%9D.%20It%20may%20restore%20faith%20in%20the%20judiciary%20to%20some%20extent%20which%20has%20largely%20echoed%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20point%20of%20view%20in%20cases%20that%20matter%20to%20the%20government%20and%20not%20held%20it%20accountable%20for%20its%20actions.%20However%2C%20the%20fight%20has%20to%20go%20on%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20Maharashtra%20government%20does%20not%20follow%20in%20the%20footsteps%20of%20the%20Gujarat%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EZoya%20Hasan%20is%20Professor%20Emerita%2C%20Centre%20for%20Political%20Studies%2C%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705401650000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F17184203%2FBILKIS-BANO-.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fbilkis-banos-long-struggle-for-justice%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Feminist%20solidarities%20came%20to%20the%20forefront%20in%20Bilkis%20Bano's%20struggle%20for%20justice%2C%20through%20legal%20petitions%2C%20street%20protests%2C%20vigils%20and%20signature%20campaigns.%20These%20solidarities%20were%20particularly%20evident%20after%20the%20remission.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fbilkis-banos-long-struggle-for-justice%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BPolitical%20Event%26quot%3B%3A%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20On%20Why%20Congress%20Is%20Skipping%20Temple%20Event%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ECongress%20leader%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20today%20said%20it%20is%20difficult%20for%20his%20party's%20leaders%20to%20attend%20the%20January%2022%20Ram%20temple%20consecration%20ceremony%20as%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20RSS%20have%20turned%20it%20into%20a%20%26quot%3Bpolitical%20event%26quot%3B%20centred%20around%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20remarks%20at%20a%20press%20conference%20during%20the%20Bharat%2