20the%20new%20Bill%20will%20prove%20%E2%80%9Cadverse%20to%20the%20spirit%20of%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20freedom%20of%20the%20press%20guaranteed%20by%20the%20constitution%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EEGI%20has%20submitted%20a%20representation%20on%20the%20draft%20Broadcasting%20Services%20Bill%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FMIB_India%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40MIB_India%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cbr%3E%5CnPrimary%20concerns%20are%20Centre%E2%80%99s%20powers%20to%20monitor%20and%20block%20content%2C%20prohibit%20transmission%20on%20vague%20grounds%2C%20and%20a%20system%20of%20self%20regulation%20that%20allows%20govt%20great%20control.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FpRvtFg2UbC%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FpRvtFg2UbC%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%20(%40IndEditorsGuild)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FIndEditorsGuild%2Fstatus%2F1746853908205498810%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJanuary%2015%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20outlined%20four%20major%20concerns%20with%20the%20upcoming%20legislation.%20The%20EGI%20said%20the%20Bill%20will%20result%20in%20an%20%E2%80%9Coverbearing%20system%20of%20self-regulation%E2%80%9D%20mandating%20the%20creation%20of%20content%20evaluation%20committees%20in%20a%20manner%20that%20allows%20the%20government%20to%20have%20a%20greater%20degree%20of%20control%20on%20those%20committees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20press%20body%20also%20feared%20that%20the%20Bill%20would%20lay%20the%20ground%20for%20the%20creation%20of%20an%20%E2%80%9Coverarching%20censorship%20framework%E2%80%9D%20through%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20broadcast%20advisory%20council%2C%20headed%20by%20a%20bureaucrat%20with%20a%20mandate%20to%20monitor%20and%20block%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20said%20the%20Bill%20will%20make%20it%20possible%20for%20the%20government%20to%20regulate%20or%20even%20prohibit%20transmission%20of%20channels%20and%20programmes%20on%20%E2%80%9Cvague%20grounds%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20EGI%20also%20feared%20that%20the%20provisions%20that%20allow%20the%20government%20%E2%80%9Cexcessive%20delegation%20of%20rule-making%20are%20problematic%E2%80%9D%20due%20to%20uncertainty%20for%20the%20stakeholders%20who%20may%20be%20impacted%20by%20the%20draft%20Bill%20and%20prevent%20individuals%20from%20being%20fully%20informed%20to%20meaningfully%20engage%20in%20the%20consultation%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETogether%20with%20the%20Internet%20Freedom%20Foundation%2C%20the%20EGI%20spelt%20out%20its%20concerns%20specific%20to%20each%20of%20the%20clauses%20mentioned%20in%20the%20Bill.%20The%20EGI%20requested%20the%20Centre%20to%20put%20the%20Bill%20under%20abeyance%20till%20all%20stakeholders%20express%20their%20views.%20The%20government%20has%20been%20eliciting%20the%20views%20of%20various%20stakeholders%20on%20the%20draft%20Bill%20since%20November%2010%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705333474000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F10%2F23203159%2FScreen-Shot-2020-10-23-at-8.31.43-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fvague-and-excessively-intrusive-editors-guild-of-india-to-centre-on-broadcast-services-bill%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20a%20letter%20to%20Union%20minister%20Anurag%20Thakur%2C%20the%20EGI%20said%20the%20draft%20Broadcast%20Services%20(Regulation)%20Bill%2C%202023%20would%20lay%20the%20ground%20for%20the%20creation%20of%20an%20'overarching%20censorship%20framework'%20through%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20broadcast%20advisory%20council.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fvague-and-excessively-intrusive-editors-guild-of-india-to-centre-on-broadcast-services-bill%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%