a.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fhomestay-4-1-1704942909.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fhomestay-4-1-1704942909-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fhomestay-4-1-1704942909-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fhomestay-4-1-1704942909-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fhomestay-4-1-1704942909-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-337996%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAshish%20was%20able%20to%20give%20life%20to%20his%20dream%20with%20the%20help%20of%20his%20friend%20Daya%20and%20local%20people.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeing%20an%20advocate%20for%20sustainable%20development%2C%20he%20went%20on%20to%20build%20his%20house%20using%20the%20traditional%20architectural%20methods%20of%20the%20Kumaon%20region.%20For%20instance%2C%20instead%20of%20using%20cement%2C%20he%20used%20mud%2C%20cow%20dung%2C%20repurposed%20old%20wood%2C%20rock%2C%20and%20stones%20to%20construct%20the%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20did%20not%20use%20cement%20at%20all.%20We%20used%20a%20mixture%20of%20mud%2C%20%3Cem%3Ebhusa%3C%2Fem%3E%20(hay)%2C%20and%20cow%20dung%20to%20make%20the%20walls.%20Additionally%2C%20I%20also%20adopted%20age-old%20practices%20of%20%3Cem%3Elipaai%20%3C%2Fem%3E%5Bpaiting%20walls%20with%20cow%20dung%20and%20water%5D.%20This%20provides%20good%20thermal%20insulation%20and%20keeps%20the%20house%20warm%20in%20winter%20and%20cool%20in%20summer%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20used%20stone%20slates%20to%20make%20slanted%20roofs%20with%20large%20sunroofs%20that%20let%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20natural%20light%20during%20the%20day.%20Sunroofs%20help%20us%20save%20energy%20as%20we%20do%20not%20need%20any%20power%20between%207%20am%20